OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1776798670
OL,3,CKing leads tributes to Queen Elizabeth
OL,4,CII on her centenary
OL,6,FThe late Queen would have turned 100
OL,7,Fon April 21, and the King said her
OL,8,Fexistence should be celebrated as a
OL,9,F"life well-lived" rather than marking
OL,10,Fan "absence" ahead of a series of
OL,11,Froyal events that will honour her on
OL,12,FTuesday.
OL,14,F"Much about the times we now live in,
OL,15,FI suspect, may have troubled her
OL,16,Fdeeply, but I take heart from her
OL,17,Fbelief that goodness will always
OL,18,Fprevail and that a brighter dawn is
OL,19,Fnever far from the horizon," the King
OL,20,Fsaid in his message.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@QO]rD@DOUrD@LO]vD@AOU{D@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
